it was flagged but the pavement had rotted and cracked under the oozing of the water
eight feet above the floor along and massive beam traversed this subterranean excavation from side to side from this beam hung at short distances a part chains three feet long and at the end of these chains there were rings for the neck
in this vault men who had been condemned to the valleys were incarcerated until the day of their departure for toulon
they were thrust under this beam where each one found his better's swinging in the darkness and waiting for him
